            "body": "> Nvim doesn't restore cursor position automatically. You need to set the cursor position to the `\"` mark to restore cursor position. `getpos('\"')` is not valid. To get the position of the `\"` mark you should use `getpos('''\"')` or `getpos(\"'\\\"\")`. `/tmp` is ignored from ShaDa as of 0.12.\n\nThank you for the quick response. I updated the autocmd to use getpos(\"'\\\"\") as suggested, but the cursor position is still not restored.\ngetpos(\"'\\\"\") returns [0, 0, 0, 0] after restarting Neovim, just like before. The shada file exists and contains the correct file path (verified via xxd), but the mark does not seem to be read correctly.\nIs there anything else I should check?",
