        {
            "author_association": "NONE",
            "body": "> Going to assume this is a problem with your environment (your shada files are in an unexpected location, or some config issue). You are not being precise in the steps you are describing, so this is a waste of our time.\n\nIt was indeed a problem with my environment (more specifically, my treesitter config). I fixed it by removing any treesitter-refs in ```init.lua``` and creating a file called ```.config/nvim/lua/plugins/treesitter.lua```:\n```lua\nreturn {\n  {\n    \"nvim-treesitter/nvim-treesitter\",\n    build = \":TSUpdate\",\n    event = \"BufReadPost\",\n    config = function()\n      require(\"nvim-treesitter.configs\").setup({\n        ensure_installed = {\n          \"c\", \"cpp\", \"lua\", \"python\", \"bash\", \"json\", \"vim\", \"markdown\",\n        },\n        auto_install = true,\n        highlight = { enable = true },\n        indent = { enable = false },\n      })\n    end,\n  },\n}\n```\nPerhaps this helps someone in the future.",
